Akwa United forward, Uche Collins is confident the club can win a second Nigeria Premier Football League title this season. The Promise Keepers are in third position on the Group A table with 15 points from nine matches. Collins joined Akwa United from Sokoto United at the start of the season. The striker has scored once in three league appearances for the Uyo club. “I will continue to give my best to ensure I score in every match I play to help my team win games and the NPFL title this season,” Collins told DAILY POST. “It’s our biggest dream this season and I believe it is achievable.”